# EquiliBot Production Roadmap And Implementation Plan

## Phase 1 Security And On-Chain Foundation
Objective: Build the legal and technical guardrails before any autonomous strategy execution.

### Contract Development (Foundry)
- [x] Implement EquiliBotModule.sol (Safe module execution boundary)
- [x] Implement SwapGuard.sol (on-chain policy engine)
- [x] Prevent dust swaps with per-token minimum trade amounts
- [x] Enforce slippage limits with owner-configurable guardrails
- [x] Enforce daily volume limits with decimal-aware scaling and per-token overrides
- [x] Enforce strict token isolation in module execution (non-swap tracked token balances cannot decrease)
- [x] Enforce canonical calldata and Safe-only recipient routing for approved selectors
- [x] Enforce per-token cooldown (not global agent-level lock)

### Security Testing
- [x] Achieve 100 percent source coverage in Foundry
- [x] Maintain fuzz coverage on checkSwap safety invariants
- [x] Add regression tests for strict isolation, recipient lock, decimal scaling, and cooldown behavior

### Deployment And Verification
- [x] Deploy to BNB testnet
- [x] Verify contracts on BscScan
- [x] Enable module in Safe
- [x] Validate live on-chain configuration against policy settings

